<p><strong>Edit</strong>:  As mentioned in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chick_tract#Dark_Dungeons" rel="nofollow">Wikipedia article</a>, an earlier version of "Dark Dungeons" (the one that was my introduction to Chick tracts a couple decades ago) listed C. S. Lewis and J. R. R. Tolkien as occult authors whose books should be burned.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2rbv"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2rbv" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2rbv')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2rbv" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2rbv')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2rbv" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2t0/rationality_quotes_october_2010/2rbv?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2rbv" href="#2rbu" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2rbv" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2rbv')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2rbv class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2rbv" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2rbv" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2rbv" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2ri4" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2ri4" class="parent"><a name="2ri4" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2ri4" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2ri4" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2ri4" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/sketerpot/">sketerpot</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 October 2010 02:39:13AM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2ri4'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2ri4')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2ri4" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span 