"return showcomment('t1_2rpx')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2rpx" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2rpx" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/James_K/">James_K</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">09 October 2010 06:07:20AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2rpx'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2rpx'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2rpx')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2rpx" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I'd go along with both of those examples (though the US has a history of corporate bailouts that extends far beyond current events).  Also rent control (it has significant perverse effects on rental markets and often hurts the poor).</p>

