="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2r81" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2r81" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/arch1/">arch1</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 October 2010 09:15:06PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2r81'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2r81')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2r81" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2r81" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/arch1/">arch1</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 October 2010 09:15:06PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2r81'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2r81'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2r81')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2r81" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Er, how about the wisdom to know whether a thing should be changed in the 1st place?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2r81"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2r81" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2r81')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2r81" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2r81')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2r81" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2t0/rationality_quotes_october_2010/2r81?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2r81" href="#2qzr" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2r81" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2r81')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2r81 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2r81" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2r81" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2r81" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2rh9" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2rh9" class="parent"><a name="2rh9" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2rh9" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2rh9" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2rh9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 October 2010 12:08:08AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2rh9'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2rh9')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2rh9" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2rh9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 October 2010 12:08:08AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2rh9'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2rh9'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2rh9')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2rh9" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>A good point... although I would remove the 'should' and instead emphasise the coherence and self awareness to know which things I want.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2rh9"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2rh9" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2rh9')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2rh9" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2rh9')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2rh9" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2t0/rationality_quotes_october_2010/2rh9?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2rh9" href="#2r81" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2rh9" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2rh9')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2rh9 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2rh9" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2r0y" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2r0y" class="parent"><a name="2r0y" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2r0y" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2r0y" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2r0y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Unnamed/">Unnamed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 October 2010 02:00:55AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2r0y'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2r0y')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2r0y" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2r0y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Unnamed/">Unnamed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 October 2010 02:00:55AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2r0y'>9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2r0y'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2r0y')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2r0y" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>What I like about the serenity prayer (at least the way I interpret it) is that it puts the priority on changing things; serenity is just a second-best option for things that are unchangeable.</p>

<p>In that respect, it's like a transhumanist slogan.  With something like life extension, I want to point to the serenity prayer and say we can change this, which means we need to have the courage to change.  Death at the end of the current lifespan isn't something that we should serenely accept because <em>we can</em> change it.  The serenity prayer calls for courage and action to follow through and make those changes.</p>

<p>Part of the difficulty is that the wisdom to know the difference also requires the wisdom to change your mind.  Once people accept that something cannot be changed, then their serenity-producing mechanisms prevent them from reconsidering the evidence and recognizing that maybe it really can (and should) be changed.</p>

<p>If I was going to alter the serenity prayer, that's one thing I'd add.  In Alicorn's version, that means the strength as a rationalist to distinguish what I can and cannot change, and to update those categorizations as new evidence arises.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2r0y"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2r0y" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2r0y')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2r0y" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2r0y')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2r0y" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2t0/rationality_quotes_october_2010/2r0y?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2r0y" href="#2qzr" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2r0y" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2r0y')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2r0y class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2r0y" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2r0y" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2r0y" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2r1e" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2r1e" class="parent"><a name="2r1e" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2r1e" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2r1e" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2r1e" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Mass_Driver/">Mass_Driver</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 October 2010 04:12:53AM</span><span class="votes " >11 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2r1e'] = ['10 points', '11 points', '12 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2r1e')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2r1e" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2r1e" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Mass_Driver/">Mass_Driver</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 October 2010 04:12:53AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2r1e'>11 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2r1e'] = ['10 points', '11 points', '12 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2r1e')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2r1e" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Friends, help me build the serenity to accept the things I cannot change; the courage to change the things I can; and the wisdom to continually update which is which based on the best available evidence.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2r1e"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2r1e" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2r1e')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2r1e" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2r1e')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2r1e" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2t0/rationality_quotes_october_2010/2r1e?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2r1e" href="#2r0y" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2r1e" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2r1e')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2r1e class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2r1e" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2qzw" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2qzw" class="parent"><a name="2qzw" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2qzw" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2qzw" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2qzw" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Alicorn/">Alicorn</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 October 2010 09:46:49